    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-08T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="277"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.48/1491: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-08T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 8, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>849. Department’s 775, April 5, midnight. British Embassy Lisbon has telegraphed
                    London and Madrid that Chargé called yesterday on Secretary General who informed
                    him that Salazar agreed on April 17 as evacuation date but insisted Setubal be
                    used. It is understanding of British Embassy Madrid that although British would
                    greatly prefer evacuation thru Lisbon (they now allege rail connection with
                    Setubal unsatisfactory although as a matter of fact they have nothing to do with
                    rail transportation of these refugees) they are prepared to accept Setubal which
                    they suggested originally as compromise proposal. We are still basing our
                    arrangements on arrival evacuation ships at Setubal 17th and hope for prompt
                    confirmation that Portuguese and British are in agreement not only on date but
                    on port.</p>
                <p>Repeated to London, Lisbon and Algiers for Murphy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
